it.emarolab.amor.owlInterface

Class OWLLibrary

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.emarolab.amor.owlInterface.OWLLibrary
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    OWLReferencesInterface

    public class OWLLibrary
extends java.lang.Object
    Project: aMOR
    File: it.emarolab.amor.owlInterface.OWLLibrary
    Licence: GNU GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE. Version 3, 29 June 2007
    Author: Buoncompagni Luca (luca.buoncompagni@edu.unige.it)
    affiliation: DIBRIS, EMAROLab, University of Genoa.
    date: Feb 10, 2016

    This class is the lowest interface level with the OWL API. It contains all the basic structures to manipulate ontologies but does not provide any initialization procedure.
    Initialization of this class should be done by calling (in this order): setIriFilePath(IRI), setIriOntologyPath(IRI), setManager(), createOntology() or loadOntologyFromFile(), setFactory(), setPrefixFormat() and setOWLReasoner(String, boolean, String).
    WARNING: It is recommended not to interact directly twith this class, use OWLReferences instead.

    • Constructor Detail

      • OWLLibrary

        protected OWLLibrary()
        This constructor force this class to be used only inside the aMor.owlInterface package. This object is internally used to manage OWLReferences and should not be used for other purposes. If you want to interact with the ontology use the OWLReferences instead.
        This method does not provide any initialisation procedure. Please note that before you use any other methods of this class, you must call setIriFilePath(IRI) and setIriOntologyPath(IRI) methods. For a complete initialisation of this object see the methods listed in the seeAlso section.
        See Also:
        setIriFilePath(IRI), setIriOntologyPath(IRI), setManager(), createOntology(), setFactory(), setPrefixFormat(), setOWLReasoner(String, boolean, String)

      • createOntology

        protected void createOntology()
        Creates and sets a new empty ontology in accordance with getIriOntologyPath().
        It sets the field to null if the ontology path associated to the parameter is not correct. Also, This method requires that the values: getIriOntologyPath() and getOWLManager() are not null nor badly formatted. If this happens, the ontology object associated to that class instance will be null too.

      • setOWLReasoner

        protected void setOWLReasoner(java.lang.String reasonerFactoryName,
                              boolean buffering,
                              java.lang.String loggingName)
        It creates and sets a Reasoner instance. The type of the reasoner is defined by the reasoner name factory, which could be: REASONER_QUALIFIER_PELLET, REASONER_QUALIFIER_SNOROCKET, REASONER_QUALIFIER_HERMIT or REASONER_QUALIFIER_FACT.
        If the buffering flag is true then the reasoner will update its state only if OWLReferencesInterface.synchronizeReasoner() is called. Otherwise, the reasoner will synchronise itself after every change in the ontology. The system will return null if a java reflection error occurs while instancing the class defined by the parameter reasonerFactoryName. Field getOWLOntology() has not to be null.
        Parameters:
        reasonerFactoryName - full java qualifier of the reasoner factory class to be initialised.
        buffering - if true the reasoner buffers changes.
        loggingName - for debugging. Evocative name given to the ReasonerMonitor assigned to this reasoner.

      • setPelletReasoner

        protected void setPelletReasoner(boolean buffering,
                                 java.lang.String loggingName)
        Creates and sets an instance of the Pellet reasoner by calling setOWLReasoner(String, boolean, String) with input parameter set to: REASONER_QUALIFIER_PELLET, buffering and loggingName respectively.
        Parameters:
        buffering - if true the reasoner must be synchronized manually. Else, sync is automatic.
        loggingName - for debugging. Evocative name given to the ReasonerMonitor assigned to this reasoner.

      • getOWLClass

        public org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLClass getOWLClass(java.lang.String className)
        Returns an Object which represents an ontological class with a given name and specific IRI paths. If the entity already exists in the ontology, then the object will refer to it, otherwise the method will create a new ontological entity (not automatically added to the ontology).
        Parameters:
        className - name of the ontological class.
        Returns:
        the OWL class with the given name and IRI paths, in accordance with the OWLReference.

      • getOWLLiteral

        public org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLLiteral getOWLLiteral(java.lang.Object value,
                                                             org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLDatatype type)
        Given an Object value, this method returns the OWLLiteral in accordance with the actual type of value. The parameter Type can be null (i.e., not specified) if value is of type: String, Integer, Boolean, Float, Long or OWLLiteral; otherwise it must be specified explicitly. For more specific data type this methods require to give as input the right OWLDataType parameter. WARNING: it will return null if the data type of the parameter value is unknown.
        Parameters:
        value - value of queried literal.
        type - OWL data type of queried literal.
        Returns:
        the OWL literal object with the given value, type and IRI paths, in accordance with the OWLReference.

      • callReasoning

        protected void callReasoning(java.lang.Long initialTime_ns)
        Performs reasoning on the Ontology when reasoner is set to buffering mode. It does not have any effects on non-buffering reasoners. WARNING: it does not consider pending changes on the manipulation buffer (OWLManipulator).
        Parameters:
        initialTime_ns - is only used for logging purposes in case of reasoning pre-processing.
        initialTime_ns - represents the initial time used to compute the reasoning time[ns] to be logged.

      • callReasoning

        protected void callReasoning()
        Performs reasoning on the Ontology when reasoner is set to buffering mode. It does not have any effects on non-buffering reasoners. WARNING: it does not consider pending changes on the manipulation buffer (OWLManipulator).
